## Rollback Configuration

The rollback system uses hardware watchdog + boot count tracking to
automatically revert to the previous firmware slot on boot failure.

### Triggers

1. **Watchdog Timeout** — Hardware watchdog fires if application fails to
   initialize within timeout period
2. **Boot Count Exceeded** — Bootloader increments counter each boot;
   if counter exceeds threshold, rollback is triggered
3. **Health Check Failure** — Application-level health check fails after
   boot completes

### Health Check Integration

```c
// After successful application initialization:
// 1. Pet the watchdog
// 2. Clear the boot counter
// 3. Mark the slot as good
ota_confirm_update();
```

